Further features and advantages of the present disclosure will become apparent from the following detailed description, taken in combination with the appended drawings, in which:
FIGs. 1 to 4 show representations of a graphical user interface displaying content items;
FIGs. 5 & 6 show representations of a graphical user interface displaying a content item list and an associated list of characteristics for navigation;
FIGs. 7 & 8 show representations of a graphical user interface displaying a content item list with an associated list of characteristics for navigation having a scalable navigation element;
FIG, 9 shows a method of displaying content items;
FIG. 10 shows a method of displaying and navigating a content item list;
FIG. 11 shows an alternative method of displaying and navigating a content item list; and
FIG. 12 shows schematic representation of a device for executing a graphical user interface for displaying and navigating content items.

claim.claim-text:
1. A method on an electronic device (100), the method comprising:
displaying (902, 1102) content items (116, 117, 118) each having an associated common property (116a, 117a, 118a) in a graphical user interface (1248) on a display (1218) of the electronic device (100);
displaying (904, 1104) an indicia (170) in association with the displayed content items (116, 117, 118), the indicia for identifying a position of the displayed content items (116, 117, 118) relative to the associated common property by which the content items (116, 117, 118) are ordered for display within the graphical user interface (1248);
determining (1106) a measure of the common property associated with the displayed content items (116, 117, 118); and
modifying (1108) a display element of the indicia corresponding at least in part to a distribution of the measure of the common property (116a, 117a, 118a) associated with the displayed content items (116, 117, 118) the display element of the indicia changing as the measure of the common property changes based upon positions of each of the content items displayed within the graphical user interface (1110).
